A very similar photo, perhaps of the same occasion, given that a substantial number of men can be identified in the same place, is at <a href="http://www.tipsimages.it/Photo/ShowImage_Editorial_Popup.asp?IMID=2914126&amp;ched=ed" rel="nofollow">www.tipsimages.it/Photo/ShowImage_Editorial_Popup.asp?IMI...</a>
captioned, &quot;View of the Plenary Hall of the German Reichstag during the session of September 28, 1916. Reich Chancellor Theobald Bethmann Hollweg (upper left half of the photo, standing at the governmental bench) speaks about the military and political situation.&quot;

In the Bain photo, the man is sitting and men on either side are looking towards him.  It certainly could be <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theobald_von_Bethmann-Hollweg" rel="nofollow">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theobald_von_Bethmann-Hollweg</a>

