&quot;A practicing farmer, Hernandez became the first Filipino director of the Bureau of Agriculture in 1916, which had been headed by Americans colonial officials before his tenure.[3] This was part of the Filipinization policy of the American colonial government, following the Jones Act of 1916,&quot;

