&quot;One of the most daring of American flyers was the victim of an accident which occurred on August 18 1918.  Lieutenant Alexander Blair Thaw 2d of Pittsburgh, a younger brother of the famous American ace Major William Thaw was killed when his machine developed engine trouble at an altitude of 2,000 feet and fell. Lieutenant Thaw's companion aviator Lieutenant Cord Meyer was badly injured.&quot;
The Story of The Great War, v. 16 (1920)
